Czech First League club, Viktoria Plzen have announced the signing of Nigeria forward, Rafiu Adekunle Duronsinmi on a six-month loan deal. Durosinmi linked up with Viktoria Plzen from second-division club Karvina with an option to buy included in the deal. The 20-year-old will wear jersey number 17 at his new club. The young forward trained with his new teammates for the first time on Monday and will fly with the team to Benidorm, Spain on Wednesday for a training tour. “I am happy that I got such a chance. I watched Victoria’s matches in the Champions League, they are a really big team and I have to do my best to be able to make it,” Durosinmi told the club’s official website. He joined another Nigerian, Fortune Bassey, at the club.